[2026-05-21T01:30Z] SPPARKS_baseline: structural blocker — perturbation cannot be re-enabled without coordinated vanilla+checkpointed source change (USER DECISION NEEDED)
  context: 2026-05-21T00:30Z demotion directive said "rerun with perturbation calibrated and the new gate path".
    The directive is structurally unsatisfiable for SPPARKS under the current AGENTS.md constraints.
  why: the v2.2 cold-replay gate requires the validation signature (the bytes compared between
    runs) to vary measurably under the chosen perturbation knob. SPPARKS' signature schema is the
    6-double dumpValidationSignatureBin_spparks output defined in TWO places that MUST stay
    coordinated:
