      - tests/apps/checkpointed/SPPARKS/src/main.cpp (reference checkpointed — IMMUTABLE per AGENTS.md)
    The schema currently captures only geometry + simulation-duration invariants (nsites,
    app->time, world_size, products thereof). None of these depend on temperature, RNG seed,
    or any trajectory-dependent quantity. The 2026-05-19 calibrator measured output_diff=0.0
    for temperature 0.98 vs 1.02, confirming the signature is perturbation-insensitive by
    construction. Switching the knob (seed, magnetization, boundary) cannot help, because
    the schema does not record anything trajectory-dependent.
  options for user:
    (a) Grant an AGENTS.md exemption for SPPARKS to coordinately edit the checkpointed/
        main.cpp signature to add a T-sensitive field (final energy sum_i s_i, naccept/nreject
        ratio, or final magnetization). Pros: unlocks v2.2 path. Cons: violates the "reference
        code is immutable" rule, requires re-cache of baseline_cache/SPPARKS/validation_output.bin
        + re-bench against the new signature.
    (b) Keep perturbation:disabled, accept the legacy single-point F-19 fallback as SPPARKS's
        permanent path, and document SPPARKS as a known-coverage-gap app in the paper
        methodology (cite that v2.2 gates B+C are structurally unreachable for SPPARKS due
        to its native validation schema). SPPARKS stays UNTRUSTED until F-19 re-iter+bench
        confirms it.
    (c) Drop SPPARKS from the benchmark set entirely. Pros: avoids the methodological
        asterisk. Cons: loses one of two iterative_fixed-KMC apps (the other is PRK_Stencil,
        a stencil app, different mechanism); narrows experiment coverage.
  recommendation: option (b) — keeps the AGENTS.md invariant and is the lowest-disturbance
    path; the F-19 fallback is the same gate the entire pipeline relied on pre-v2.2 and is
    sufficient to detect Patterns A'/B'/E' source-side; only Pattern D' cold-replay coverage
    is degraded for this single app. Document the gap in the paper methodology section.
  action: WAITING FOR USER. Do not run calibrator or iter for SPPARKS until decision is made.

