    auto-stripper scripts/strip_vanilla_checkpoint_hints.py:200-272 only EDITS files inside
    bench/, never deletes the directory — the deletion was a manual git rm in the same commit
    that ran the stripper, with no cross-check against the YAML's input path references.
  root cause: deep-strip workflow has no automatic guard that prevents deleting paths
    referenced by tests/apps/configs/<APP>.yaml fields (input_subdir, app_args, build.cmd
    cwd-relatives, recovery_hook paths).
  immediate fix done in this session: restored tests/apps/vanillas/LAMMPS/bench/in.lj_long from
    git blob d09ffc994472904e33b011a035f91bb0bad57068. grep restart|checkpoint on the restored
    file confirms it is clean of resilience hints (vanilla form, 30 lines).
  recommended preventive guard (NOT YET IMPLEMENTED — separate task for user approval):
    Add a pre-commit / pre-strip check that, for every <APP>.yaml under tests/apps/configs/:
      1. Resolve input_subdir + every app_args path entry that looks like a relative file path
      2. Resolve every patch path under tests/apps/patches/<APP>/
      3. Resolve build.cmd cwd-relative paths if any
      4. Refuse to delete (or warn loudly) any vanilla tree path that is referenced
